divs: Sighting DetailsSighting Report: I didn t really see a UFO but I am trying to find out about missing time. It seems that for the last three years- especially this year- that no matter how many times I reset my clocks and watches- the next day or so- the times aren t in synch any more. At first I thought it was bad batteries in my watch or alarm clock but then my husband s electric alarm clock was off too. It is not just the colcks in our house but in my car as well. I am always resetting it or resetting my watch to match my car- or something of the sorts. Is there a natural phenom as to why our "time" keeps getting fragged? Is there something magnetic in the ground that would cause this? Or am I just paranoid because I am begginning to never know what time it really is?! My husband thinks I am crazy for researching this and trying to find answers. He thinks I am just over tired from working and balancing time with our infant son. This "missing time" started before I was pregnant- and got more noticable recently. Maybe he is right and I am just being over-reactive. I would still like a second opinion.
